---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Pear Notes" description="Pear Notes Privacy Policy. We collect zero data. Your notes are encrypted on-device and synced peer-to-peer.">
  <div class="dot-grid"></div>
  <Header />

  <section class="legal container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: June 28, 2026</p>

    <p>
      Pear Notes ("we", "our", or "the app") is committed to protecting your privacy.
      This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use the Pear Notes
      application on any platform (iOS, Android, macOS, Windows).
    </p>

    <h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>We do not collect any personal data.</strong> Pear Notes is built on a
      zero-knowledge architecture. All your notes, voice recordings, document scans,
      and media are created, stored, and encrypted entirely on your device. We have no
      servers that receive, process, or store your content.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data Storage</h2>
    <p>
      All data is stored locally on your device in an encrypted database. Specifically:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Notes and text content</strong> — Stored in a local encrypted database on your device.</li>
      <li><strong>Voice recordings</strong> — Saved in an encrypted media vault on your device's local storage.</li>
      <li><strong>Document scans and images</strong> — Stored in the same encrypted media vault.</li>
      <li><strong>Backups</strong> — Exported as AES-256 encrypted .pnbk files that you control. These files can only be decrypted with your unique 64-character private key.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data Synchronization</h2>
    <p>
      Pear Notes uses <strong>peer-to-peer (P2P) synchronization</strong> to sync your data
      between your own devices. This means:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your data is transmitted directly between your devices over encrypted channels.</li>
      <li>No third-party cloud servers are used to store or relay your content.</li>
      <li>Device pairing uses a secure blind handshake with cryptographic identity verification via QR codes.</li>
      <li>All data in transit is end-to-end encrypted.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
      Pear Notes does not integrate with any third-party analytics, advertising,
      tracking, or data collection services. We do not use:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Google Analytics or any analytics SDK</li>
      <li>Advertising networks or ad SDKs</li>
      <li>Crash reporting services that collect personal data</li>
      <li>Social media tracking pixels</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Device Permissions</h2>
    <p>
      Pear Notes requests the following device permissions, used solely for in-app functionality:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Camera</strong> — Used to scan physical documents and to scan QR codes for secure device pairing. Camera data is processed on-device and never transmitted externally.</li>
      <li><strong>Microphone</strong> — Used to record voice notes. Audio is saved locally in the encrypted media vault and never sent to external servers.</li>
      <li><strong>Storage / File Access</strong> — Used to export and import encrypted backup archives (.pnbk files). Files are managed locally by you.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>We do not share any data with third parties.</strong> Since we do not collect
      or have access to your data, there is nothing to share. Your notes, recordings,
      and documents remain exclusively on your devices.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Data Retention & Deletion</h2>
    <p>
      Since all data is stored locally on your device:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>You have full control over your data at all times.</li>
      <li>You can delete individual notes, recordings, or scans at any time from within the app.</li>
      <li>You can wipe all app data from the settings menu.</li>
      <li>Uninstalling the app removes all locally stored data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Pear Notes does not knowingly collect any information from children under the age
      of 13. Since we collect no data from any user, there are no special provisions
      required. The app is suitable for users of all ages.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Security</h2>
    <p>
      We take security seriously. Pear Notes employs:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>AES-256 encryption</strong> for all stored data and backup files.</li>
      <li><strong>End-to-end encrypted P2P channels</strong> for device synchronization.</li>
      <li><strong>Cryptographic blind pairing</strong> to prevent identity leaks during device linking.</li>
      <li><strong>Encrypted media vault</strong> with an isolated streaming server to prevent cache leaks.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted
      on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. Since we do not collect user
      contact information, we cannot notify you directly — we encourage you to review
      this page periodically.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:amreshcse007@gmail.com">amreshcse007@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
